ing the potential for ?blended finance? (linking aid with loans from public=
ly-owned institutions or commercial lenders) to help achieve the sustainabl=
e development goals.

He pointed out that, as recently as 2016, more than half of all reported co=
ntracts were still awarded to firms in the donor country. ?Donors not only =
need to untie all aid, but also make sure that their procurement practices =
are tailored towards the private sector in developing countries,? he said.

Claire Godfrey, interim director of policy, advocacy and research at Bond, =
